        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 24 at 2:40PM MDT by NWS North Platte NE</headline>
        <description>At 240 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Grant, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Grant, Madrid, and Elsie.

This includes Highway 61 between mile markers 47 and 70.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
